'''Anass Salah-Eddine'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifadata.com/documents/FU17WC/2019/pdf/FU17WC_2019_Squadlists.pdf |title=FIFA U-17 World Cup Brazil 2019: List of Players: Netherlands |publisher=FIFA |page=16 |date=31 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191227222540/https://www.fifadata.com/documents/FU17WC/2019/pdf/FU17WC_2019_Squadlists.pdf |archive-date=27 December 2019}}</ref> ({{Langx|ar|أنس صلاح الدين}}; born 18 January 2002) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] or [[left wing-back]] for {{Dutch football updater|PSVEindho}} club [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]], on loan from {{Italian football updater|Roma}} club [[AS Roma|Roma]], and the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]].

== Club career ==
Salah-Eddine's youth career started with [[Jong Ajax]] in 2018. On 1 August 2022, he signed a contract extension until the end of the 2025 season. He then joined [[FC Twente|Twente]] on loan for the [[2022–23 FC Twente season|2022–23 season]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Contractverlenging en verhuur voor Anass Salah-Eddine |url=https://www.ajax.nl/artikelen/contractverlenging-en-verhuur-anass-salah-eddine/ |access-date=1 August 2022 |website=www.ajax.nl |language=nl-NL}}</ref> On 1 February 2024, he joined Twente on a permanent deal until 2027.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Anass Salah-Eddine naar FC Twente |url=https://fctwente.nl/nieuws/anass-salah-eddine-naar-fc-twente |access-date=1 February 2024 |website=fctwente.nl |language=nl-NL}}</ref>

On 3 February 2025, Salah-Eddine joined [[Serie A]] club [[AS Roma|Roma]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.asroma.com/en/news/72754/anass-salah-eddine-joins-roma |title=Anass Salah-Eddine joins Roma |publisher=AS Roma |date=3 February 2025 }}</ref>

On 31 August 2025, Salah-Eddine returned to the Netherlands and joined reigning champions [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]], on an initial one-year loan with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=PSV Eindhoven|url=https://www.psv.nl/en/media/artikel/transfer-psv-verwelkomt-anass-salah-eddine|title=Transfer {{!}} PSV welcomes Anass Salah-Eddine|date=31 August 2025|access-date=10 September 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in the Netherlands, Salah-Eddine is of [[Morocco|Moroccan]] descent. He is a youth international for the Netherlands.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://lionsdelatlas.ma/2457470-au-moins-41-marocains-en-deuxieme-division-neerlandaise|title=Au moins 41 Marocains en deuxième division néerlandaise|date=20 August 2019}}{{Dead link|date=February 2022 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> On 21 October 2025, his request to switch international allegiance to Morocco was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref name="FIFA-CAP">{{cite news|url=https://knowledge.fifa.com/change-of-association-platform|title=FIFA Change of Association Platform|website=knowledge.fifa.com|date=21 October 2025|access-date=21 October 2025}}</ref>

On 11 December 2025, Salah-Eddine was called up to the Morocco squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/morocco-name-star-studded-afcon-squad-as-hakimi-makes-cut-but-diop-misses-out/|title=Morocco name star-studded AFCON squad as Hakimi makes cut but Diop misses out|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=11 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

